RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 2
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation or Other Sources Service
Seller provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation or Other Sources Service ("Reactive Service") from its natural gas and oil-fired electric generating facility located in Hazle Township, Luzerne County, Pennsylvania ("Facility"), to the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") system. This Rate Schedule sets forth Seller's revenue requirement for the provision of Reactive Service from the Facility to PJM ("Revenue Requirement"). This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission ("Commission").
REACTIVE SERVICE REVENUE REQUIREMENT
Effective on the date authorized by the Commission, the Revenue Requirement shall be:
Revenue Requirement Monthly Revenue Requirement $41,444.50 Annual Revenue Requirement $497,334.00
